14":"1250–1314","1263–Female":"1263–Overleden","1300–1400":"1300–1400","1210–1272":"1210–1272","1210–Female":"1210–Overleden","1314":"1314","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1263":"1263","1250":"1250","1272":"1272","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Spaxton, Somerset, England":"Spaxton, Somerset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Enmore, Somerset, England":"Enmore, Somerset, England"},"en":{"1250–1314":"1250–1314","1263–Female":"1263–Deceased","1300–1400":"1300–1400","1210–1272":"1210–1272","1210–Female":"1210–Deceased","1314":"1314","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1263":"1263","1250":"1250","1272":"1272","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Spaxton, Somerset, England":"Spaxton, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Enmore, Somerset, England":"Enmore, Somerset, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fichett","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from Old French <i>Fichet</i>, <i>Fichot</i>, or (in northern France) <i>Fiket</i>, <i>Fikot</i>, diminutive forms of <i>fiche</i> or <i>fike</i> ‘pointed implement for fixing or transfixing something or someone’ (such as a spear?), used as a nickname and as a personal name. See   Fitch  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Fickett","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Fitchett  .","Possibly an Americanized form of German   Fickert  ."]},{"name":"Fitch","meanings":["from Old French <i>fiche</i>, perhaps ‘pointed implement for fixing or transfixing something or someone’ (such as a lance?), a derivative of Old French <i>fichier</i> ‘to fix, fasten, pin on, stick into, pierce’. Compare Modern French <i>fiche</i> ‘peg, pin’. Reaney remarks that ‘as Hugh <i>Malet</i> is said to have abandoned for a time his nickname ‘little hammer’ in favor of <i>Fichet</i> (see   Mallet  ), <i>fiche</i> must have been used of a pointed weapon, a spear or lance, and <i>Fitch</i> and <i>Fitchett</i> (see   Fitchett  ) of a spearman or a knight famous for his exploits with the lance’. Use of <i>Fiche</i> as a personal name is possibly implied by diminutive personal name forms such as <i>Fechet</i> (see   Fitchett  ) and <i>Fechel</i>, attested in <i>Fechel</i> de Fercalahn, 1225–50. The latter is perhaps the source of the now extinct English surname <b>Fetchell</b>.","occasionally a variant of   Fitz  .","English:"]}]},{"name":"Hugh","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Hugues</i>, <i>Hugo</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>hug</i> ‘heart, mind, spirit’. It was originally a short form of various compound names containing this element. This was borne by the aristocracy of medieval France, adopted by the Normans, and introduced by them to Britain. It was consistently one of the most popular boys' names in the Middle Ages in England, but fell out of favour in the 16th century until it was revived in the 20th century. Little Hugh of Lincoln was a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hugh Fichett was born in 1250, in Enmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert Fichett, was 40 and his mother, Sarah Estane, was 40. He married Aubrey Conteville in 1298, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1314, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1250–1314":"1250–1314","1263–Female":"1263–Surnud","1300–1400":"1300–1400","1210–1272":"1210–1272","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1314":"1314","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1263":"1263","1250":"1250","1272":"1272","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Spaxton, Somerset, England":"Spaxton, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Enmore, Somerset, England":"Enmore, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"1250–1314":"1250–1314","1263–Female":"1263–Kuollut","1300–1400":"1300–1400","1210–1272":"1210–1272","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1314":"1314","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1263":"1263","1250":"1250","1272":"1272","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Spaxton, Somerset, England":"Spaxton, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Enmore, Somerset, England":"Enmore, Somerset, England"},"fr":{"1250–1314":"1250–1314","1263–Female":"1263–Décédée","1300–1400":"1300–1400","1210–1272":"1210–1272","1210–Female":"1210–Décédée","1314":"1314","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1263":"1263","1250":"1250","1272":"1272","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Spaxton, Somerset, England":"Spaxton, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Enmore, Somerset, England":"Enmore, Somerset, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Hugh Fichett est né en 1250, à Enmore, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Robert Fichett, avait 40 ans et sa mère, Sarah Estane, avait 40 ans. Il a épousé Aubrey Conteville en 1298, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1314, à Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 64 ans."},"de":{"1250–1314":"1250–1314","1263–Female":"1263–Verstorben","1300–1400":"1300–1400